.TH DIAGNET 1 "2026-05-13" "BusyBox-Diag" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
diagnet \- procfs-based Linux network connection monitoring tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B diagnet
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diagnet
passively reads TCP and UDP connection metadata exported by the Linux kernel
through
.IR /proc/net/tcp " and " /proc/net/udp ,
and produces connection listings, TCP state summaries, listening-port
observation, and heuristic suspicious-port flagging.
.PP
.B diagnet
does not actively probe remote endpoints, does not capture packets, and is
not an intrusion detection system. The
.B \-\-suspicious
flag implements
.IR "heuristic-based suspicious listening port observation"
only.
.PP
Connection metadata collection is delegated to the shared
.B libdiag
measurement layer;
.B diagnet
itself implements analysis, filtering, policy, and presentation.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Filtering
.TP
.BI \-\-proto " PROTO"
Filter by protocol:
.BR tcp ", " udp ", or " all
(default
.BR all ).
.TP
.BI \-\-state " STATE"
Filter by TCP state (e.g.
.BR ESTABLISHED ", " LISTEN ", " TIME_WAIT ).
Invalid state name exits with code 2.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-listen .
.TP
.B \-\-listen
Shortcut for
.BR "\-\-state LISTEN" .
.TP
.BI \-\-local-port " PORT"
Filter by local port (1..65535).
.TP
.BI \-\-remote-port " PORT"
Filter by remote port (1..65535).
.TP
.BI \-\-local-addr " ADDR"
Filter by local IPv4 address (string match).
.TP
.BI \-\-remote-addr " ADDR"
Filter by remote IPv4 address (string match).
.TP
.B \-\-suspicious
Show only listening ports flagged by the suspicious-port heuristic.
.TP
.BI \-\-whitelist " PORTS"
Comma-separated list of additional ports to add to the suspicious-port
whitelist (e.g.
.IR 8888,9090 ).
Additive only; the built-in 27-port whitelist is not replaced.
.SS Output
.TP
.BI \-\-output " FORMAT"
Output format:
.BR table " (default), " raw ", or " json .
.TP
.BI \-\-sort " MODE"
Sort records by
.BR state ", " local-port ", or " remote-port .
.TP
.B \-\-no-header
Suppress the header row in
.B table
and
.B raw
output.
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Show only the state-distribution summary. Uses streaming aggregation and
does not retain individual records in memory.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress global warnings on stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH OUTPUT FORMATS
.SS Table (default)
.nf
PROTO LOCAL_ADDR        LPORT  REMOTE_ADDR      RPORT  STATE        FLAGS
tcp   127.0.0.1         22     0.0.0.0          0      LISTEN       -
tcp   0.0.0.0           8080   0.0.0.0          0      LISTEN       suspicious_port,public_listen
udp   0.0.0.0           53     0.0.0.0          0      -            -
.fi
UDP records show STATE as
.RB \(lq - \(rq;
multiple flags are comma-joined.
.SS Raw
Same columns, single-space separated, no alignment, no header. Designed
for
.BR awk (1)
and
.BR cut (1)
pipelines.
.SS JSON
Stable schema with three top-level keys:
.B connections
(array),
.B summary
(object with
.BR total ", " tcp ", " udp ", " states "),"
and
.B warnings
(array of system-level observations such as
.BR many_time_wait ).
Each connection has
.BR protocol ", " local_address ", " local_port ", "
.BR remote_address ", " remote_port ", " state ", and " flags .
UDP records always emit
.B "state: \(dqNONE\(dq" .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, or
.B \-\-help
shown.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error: failed to read
.IR /proc/net/tcp " or " /proc/net/udp ,
or memory allocation failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error: unknown flag, invalid argument value, or mutually-exclusive
flags specified together.
.TP
.B 3
Unsupported feature (reserved for future use).
.PP
Normal output goes to stdout; errors and warnings go to stderr.
.SH EXAMPLES
List every TCP/UDP connection:
.PP
.RS
.EX
diagnet
.EE
.RE
.PP
Show listening sockets only, no header, machine-friendly columns:
.PP
.RS
.EX
diagnet \-\-listen \-\-output raw \-\-no-header
.EE
.RE
.PP
Filter by local port and inspect with
.BR jq (1):
.PP
.RS
.EX
diagnet \-\-local-port 22 \-\-output json | jq .connections
.EE
.RE
.PP
Show only heuristic-flagged listening ports, with an extended whitelist:
.PP
.RS
.EX
diagnet \-\-suspicious \-\-whitelist 8888,9090
.EE
.RE
.PP
Streaming state-distribution summary (no record retention):
.PP
.RS
.EX
diagnet \-\-stats
.EE
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /proc/net/tcp
Source of TCP connection metadata.
.TP
.I /proc/net/udp
Source of UDP connection metadata.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ss (8),
.BR netstat (8),
.BR proc (5)
